{
  "document_id": "job-35",
  "title": "Job 35",
  "type": "scripture",
  "translation": "NRSVue",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "block_id": "job-35-heading-elihu-condemns-self-",
      "type": "heading",
      "text": "Elihu Condemns Self-Righteousness"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-35-1",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 1,
      "text": "Elihu continued and said:"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-35-2",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 2,
      "text": "“Do you think this to be just?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-35-3",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 3,
      "text": "If you ask, ‘What advantage have I?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-35-4",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 4,
      "text": "I will answer you"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-35-5",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 5,
      "text": "Look at the heavens and see;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-35-6",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 6,
      "text": "If you have sinned, what do you accomplish against him?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-35-7",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 7,
      "text": "If you are righteous, what do you give to him,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-35-8",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 8,
      "text": "Your wickedness affects others like you,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-35-9",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 9,
      "text": "“Because of the multitude of oppressions people cry out;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-35-10",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 10,
      "text": "But no one says, ‘Where is God my Maker,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-35-11",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 11,
      "text": "who teaches us more than the animals of the earth"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-35-12",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 12,
      "text": "There they cry out, but he does not answer,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-35-13",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 13,
      "text": "Surely God does not hear an empty cry,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-35-14",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 14,
      "text": "How much less when you say that you do not see him,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-35-15",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 15,
      "text": "And now, because his anger does not punish"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-35-16",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 16,
      "text": "Job opens his mouth in empty talk;"
    }
  ]
}